{
  "title": "Harden REST APIs using FastAPI with Python 3.12+",
  "summary": "This guide provides a comprehensive overview of how to secure and harden REST APIs using the modern web framework, FastAPI, in conjunction with Python 3.12+.",
  "key_points": [
    "Implement OAuth2 authentication for API access control",
    "Use secure protocols like HTTPS for encrypted data transmission",
    "Follow best practices for input validation and error handling",
    "Implement rate limiting to prevent abuse and denial-of-service attacks",
    "Utilize Dependency Injection (DI) for modular and testable code",
